item.title: Nothing But Trouble
item.description: When the neighbor’s cat found out that the ginger kitten was called Woof, he scratched its back on the chimney of the neighbor’s house and said: “I would not advise a kitten with that name to go down into the courtyard. If he did, only troubles would await.” The kitten Gav heard and thought: “What kind of troubles and why are they waiting for me?” Woof immediately went down to the courtyard and carefully examined all the nooks and crannies - there were no troubles anywhere.
